software mtzweb stanford edu skip to main content home login home news people research publications software navigation research people publications a component of the work done in our group focuses on the development of advanced quantum chemistry and molecular dynamics software terachem a portion of the group is devoted to enabling quantum chemistry and first principles dynamics for molecular materials and biological molecules our focus is speed and we achieve this through redesign of modern algorithms for stream processors like the cuda enabled gpu architectures from nvidia these developments are implemented in the commercially available software program terachem from petachem llc aims excited state dynamics projects in the group involve the development and application of the ab initio multiple spawning aims program that interfaces with other quantum chemistry codes aims requires as input the potential energy surface gradients and nonadiabatic coupling matrix elements at arbitrary nuclear positions for each time step the values of the potential energy surfaces and their analytical gradients can be obtained with the mspt2 method as implemented in molpro
